{{page-title "Documentation — Job Applications"}}
<div class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl py-6 px-4 space-y-6">

  <Panel::Card>
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">Job Applications</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-600">
      A Job Application is your record of actually applying to a job. It links a Job Post to
      your resume, tracks your status through the process, and keeps notes, dates, and linked
      Q&A in one place. When the recruiter calls, you'll have the full picture.
    </p>
    {{!-- <img src="" alt="screenshot of the job applications list" /> --}}
  </Panel::Card>

  <Panel::Card>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Application Status Lifecycle</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">Track where you are in the process with these status stages:</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 text-sm">
      <span class="bg-gray-100 text-gray-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Draft</span>
      <span class="text-gray-400">→</span>
      <span class="bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Submitted</span>
      <span class="text-gray-400">→</span>
      <span class="bg-yellow-100 text-yellow-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Phone Screen</span>
      <span class="text-gray-400">→</span>
      <span class="bg-purple-100 text-purple-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Interview</span>
      <span class="text-gray-400">→</span>
      <span class="bg-green-100 text-green-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Offer</span>
      <span class="text-gray-400">→</span>
      <span class="bg-emerald-100 text-emerald-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Accepted</span>
    </div>
    <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mt-3">
      Applications that don't progress can be marked Rejected or Withdrawn at any stage.
    </p>
    {{!-- <img src="" alt="screenshot of application detail with status history" /> --}}
  </Panel::Card>

  <Panel::Card>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">What Gets Tracked</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-1 text-gray-600 text-sm list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong>Applied date</strong> — when you submitted</li>
      <li><strong>Status</strong> — current stage in the process</li>
      <li><strong>Tracking URL</strong> — link to the ATS portal or confirmation page</li>
      <li><strong>Notes</strong> — anything worth remembering: recruiter name, compensation discussed, red flags</li>
      <li><strong>Linked resume</strong> — which version you applied with</li>
      <li><strong>Linked cover letter</strong> — the letter you submitted</li>
      <li><strong>Questions &amp; Answers</strong> — application questions you were asked and your responses</li>
    </ul>
  </Panel::Card>

  <Panel::Card>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Example Application</h2>
    <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded p-4 text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-2">
      <div><span class="font-semibold">Role:</span> Senior Full-Stack Engineer at Acme Corp</div>
      <div><span class="font-semibold">Applied:</span> March 29, 2026</div>
      <div>
        <span class="font-semibold">Status:</span>
        <span class="bg-yellow-100 text-yellow-700 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full text-xs ml-1">Phone Screen</span>
      </div>
      <div><span class="font-semibold">Notes:</span> Spoke with recruiter Sarah Chen on April 3 — warm call, 45 min.
        Comp range $160–185k. Team is 6 engineers, fully remote. Next step: technical screen with hiring manager.</div>
    </div>
    {{!-- <img src="" alt="screenshot of an application in the show view" /> --}}
  </Panel::Card>

</div>
